cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with object tracking, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The proposed method also involves optimization and fusion of multiple cues, which suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The use of optimization techniques and the focus on performance evaluation suggests the involvement of machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics) likely categories. Finally, the use of adaptive fuzzy fusion model and the focus on convergence and reliability suggest the involvement of control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
